The paper deals with video inpainting, which involves filling in missing or corrupted parts of a video. This is a problem that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM), as well as graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a new algorithm that optimizes a global, patch-based functional to deal with complex scenes, which suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization techniques. The paper also emphasizes the speed and ease of implementation of the algorithm, which could be relevant to graphics and artificial intelligence.
